 "awd_abstract_narration": "A comprehensive set of new algorithmic and scientific\u00a0computing tools to numerically investigate the\u00a0modeling of\u00a0binary black hole collisions\u00a0with higher efficiency will be developed. Symbolic manipulation tools to\u00a0automatize and obtain higher order post-Newtonian expansions of the Einstein equations using\u00a0techniques from Quantum Field Theory will be developed. \u00a0The use of heterogeneous computing and, more specifically,\u00a0general purpose Graphics Processing Units (GPUs) in numerical relativity will be explored.\u00a0\r\n\r\nThe tools developed in this project aim to explore the physics of binary black hole collisions, expected to be one of the main sources of gravitational waves to be detected by ground- and space-based interferometers such as LIGO and LISA.\u00a0The parameter space is so large that new computing paradigms are needed to explore it. The results of this project should\u00a0be of interest in the broad areas of general relativity, gravitational waves,\u00a0symbolic computing algebra, field theory, and high performance computing.\u00a0",
